<B><BR>
EXCEPTIONAL CHILDREN</B><BR>
Circulation 58,000<P>
Exceptional Children (CEC), published four times a year, contains timely articles on the critical and controversial issues in special education as well as leading articles on research and developments in the field.<P>
For over 60 years, EC has been the most respected scholarly journal in the special education field, delivering an extremely dedicated readership to advertisers.<P>
<B>WHO READS EC?</B><BR>
Key decision makers in special education who buy and support those products and companies they know and trust.  You will reach:<P>
o School Administrators<BR>
o Directors and Supervisors<BR>
o Principals<BR>
o University Teacher Educators <BR>
o Researchers<BR>
o Psychologists<BR>
o Diagnosticians<BR>
o Graduate and Undergraduate Students<BR>
o Consultants<BR>
o Teachers<P>
